ition/Lebesgue.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.LebesgueDecomposition.measurableLE\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Measure</span>.<span class=\"name\">LebesgueDecomposition</span>.<span class=\"name\">measurableLE</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">μ </span><span class=\"fn\">ν</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.Measure\">Measure</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ENNReal/Basic.html#ENNReal\">ENNReal</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given two measures `μ` and `ν`, `measurableLE μ ν` is the set of measurable\nfunctions `f`, such that, for all measurable sets `A`, `∫⁻ x in A, f x ∂μ ≤ ν A`.\n\nThis is useful for the Lebesgue decomposition theorem. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Decomposition/Lebesgue.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.LebesgueDecomposition.measurableLE","kind":"def","line":768,"name":"MeasureTheory.Measure.LebesgueDecomposition.measurableLE","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Decomposition/Lebesgue.lean#L768-L773"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name