, while `MeasureTheory.Measure.eq_singularPart` provides the uniqueness of the\n`singularPart`. Here, the uniqueness is given in terms of the measures, while the uniqueness in\nterms of the functions is given in `eq_rnDeriv`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Decomposition/Lebesgue.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.eq_withDensity_rnDeriv","kind":"theorem","line":518,"name":"MeasureTheory.Measure.eq_withDensity_rnDeriv","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Decomposition/Lebesgue.lean#L518-L561"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Decomposition/Lebesgue.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.measure_sub_rnDeriv\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Measure</span>.<span class=\"name\">measure_sub_rnDeriv</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">μ </span><span class=\"fn\">ν</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.Measure\">Measure</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Decomposition/Lebesgue.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.HaveLebesgueDecomposition\">HaveLebesgueDecomposition